Use a stacked bar chart when you have multiple groupings and are interested in the proportions between values in each grouping, as well as each grouping's total.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

For example, to compare the status of leads by campaign in a report, and also to compare the totals for each status, set record count as the X-axis, status as the Y-axis, and campaign as the Groupings value.
title: Creating Stacked Bar Charts in Salesforce
